			<div id="tribute-info">
				<p>Brian Kernighan is a brilliant man. Here are some random points about him from his Wikipedia article:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Brian Kernighan is good at computers. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sQB2NjhJHvY" target="_blank">What's a computer?</a></li>
					<li>He was born in Toronto, Canada, on <time datetime="1942-01-01">January 1, 1942</time>.</li>
					<li>He studied at the University of Toronto and Princeton University.</li>
					<li>He is coauthor of the famous text <em>The C Programming Language</em>, which introduces the reader to C. C is commonly referred to as the <em>lingua franca</em> of programming languages.</li>
					<li>He helped develop Unix while working at Bell Laboratories.</li>
					<li>The 'K' in the programming language AWK stands for Kernighan.
				</ul>
				<p>A wealth of information is available on the <a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brian_Kernighan" target="_blank">Wikipedia article about Brian Kernighan</a>.</p>
			</div>
